VSCode Theme: Dark Modern


; This is a valid script comment and completely dark green.
# This is not a valid script comment since comments must start with a semicolon.
some line start ; Comments are only highlighted at line start.


;PRIMARY SECTIONS:

; Keywords to include code from other files are purple:
; There is not yet a specification that only an exactly one string expression is allowed afterwards.
importlib ""
include_insert ""
include_append ""
sub ""
importlib
importlib "" "" "" some words


; Variable names and script configs are light blue.
$myVar$
setloglevel=8
; Strings are orange.
'str'
; Booleans are not highlighted yet since they are only half valid data types in opsi-script.
true
; Numbers are highlighted although they are only half valid data types in opsi-script.
5.1
; Script functions and statements are yellow.
getos
takestring()
comment ""
exitwindows /immediatereboot
; TODO: Allow any number of spaces.
exitwindows  /immediatereboot
; Other functions are turquoise.
mytestdeffunc()
; TODO: Script constants outside of strings should not be highlighted since this is invalid syntax!
%scriptpath%
; Script constants inside of strings are light blue like variables.
; TODO: Highlight variables equally in secondary sections and differently in primary sections due to the automatic replacement!
"%scriptpath%"
; Variables inside of strings are not highlighted.
"$myVar$"
; Random non-keyword words are not highlighted, i.e. white.
random


; Keywords are dark blue:
defvar defstringlist set
if else elseif endif
and or not
switch case defaultcase endcase endswitch
for in to do
deffunc endfunc
; What TODO with defined function return types?
void string stringlist


